  "title": "Pest Control Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><em>Job details</em></u></p>\n<p>· Part-time</p>\n<p>· $1800 - $2200 (Negotiable)</p>\n<p>· Duration: 3 months</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><em>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</em></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Carry out pest management services and treatments at various locations and properties</li>\n  <li>Spray, fog, bait and trap to control pests.</li>\n  <li>Control roaches, ants, rodents, birds, termites, etc.</li>\n  <li>Inspect property, determine problem and implement the most effective solution.</li>\n  <li>Receive work orders and work requests, determine nature of the problem and undertake necessary actions.</li>\n  <li>Ensure safety of clients and their respective customers while performing duties.</li>\n  <li>Operate spraying equipment, bait gun, power fogger and various power and hand tools in performance of duties.</li>\n  <li>Comply to workplace safety regulation while executing the duties and maintenance of the equipment and vehicle</li>\n  <li>Perform other related work as instructed by reporting officer</li>\n  <li>To advise clients on pest management’s best practices and problems</li>\n  <li>Manage client’s services and reports</li>\n  <li>Any other ad-hoc duties</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><em>Job Requirements</em></u></p>\n<p>· Preferably candidates who are able to start work on short notice.</p>\n<p>· With vector control licence and class 3 driving license</p>",
